Project 02 - Windows Failed Login Detection (Brute Force Monitoring)
Objective
To monitor and alert on unauthorized login attempts (Event ID 4625) using Wazuh SIEM to detect potential brute-force activities on a Windows endpoint.
Lab Environment
•	Wazuh Server
•	Windows 10 Endpoint
•	Wazuh Agent
•	Windows Security Event Logs
Tasks Performed
1.	Configured Audit Policy: Modified Windows Local Security Policy to enable "Audit Logon Events" (Failure).
2.	Log Integration: Ensured Wazuh Agent is successfully forwarding Windows Security logs to the Wazuh Manager.
3.	Threat Simulation: Performed intentional failed login attempts (Event ID 4625) to trigger security events.
4.	Detection & Analysis: Filtered logs in the Wazuh Discover dashboard to isolate and verify the authentication failure events.
Results
•	Successfully captured and visualized multiple failed login attempts.
•	Verified that the SIEM correctly identifies and logs authentication failures in real-time.
•	The monitoring pipeline is confirmed to be operational for detecting suspicious authentication patterns.
